Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setRailPrototypeMode(25.10)                        setRailPrototypeMode(25.10)

Name
       setRailPrototypeMode - Sets the mode for Power Aware Congestion Estima-
       tion (PACE)

Syntax
        setRailPrototypeMode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-domain {{<PD1 float net1>} {<PD2 float net2>}..}]

       [-railModel {virtual | existing}]

       [-totalPower <float>]

       Sets  the mode for Power Aware Congestion Estimation (PACE). This helps
       in estimating the routability by taking into account power rail  effect
       so that congestion estimation can be done without actually building the
       power plan.  It supports multiple power domains specified in floorplan.

       Note: setRailPrototypeMode command must be called before any congestion
       estimation command is called for it to take effect.

Parameters
       -domain {{<PD1 float net1>} {<PD2 float net2>}...}
              Specifies  the  power, in milliwatts, assigned for nets in power
              domains.

              Note: If the total power or the domain power is  not  specified,
              the  setRailPrototypeMode  command  will  estimate it internally
              based on the instance area.

              Default: " " (empty string)

              Data_type: string

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each setRailPrototypeMode parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command man setRailPrototypeMode.

       -railModel {virtual | existing}
              Specifies the power grid to use.

              * virtual: Use routing blockages to model  virtual  power  grid.
                These  routing blockages are removed after congestion analysis
                is done.

              * existing: Use the current power grid.

              Default: existing

              Data_type: enums={virtual existing}

       -reset Restores all parameters modified using  setRailPrototypeMode  to
              their  default  settings. The -reset parameter must be the first
              parameter specified. If you specify -reset by itself, the  soft-
              ware resets all setRailPrototypeMode parameters to their default
              values. If you specify parameters after -reset, the software re-
              sets only those parameters to their default values.

              Any  values  that do not already match the default value and are
              reset will be reported.

       -totalPower <float>
              Specifies a target value for the power, in milliwatts,  consumed
              by the design.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: float

Related Information
              * getRailPrototypeMode

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

